<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Recognizes Victory of Sassou Nguesso </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 16 (Xinhua) -- France today formally recognized
the victory of General Denis Sassou Nguesso in the four-month war
in the Congo Republic.
</P>
<P>
"The power, from now on, is in the hands of Sassou Nguesso,"
said the French State Secretary of Cooperation, Charles
Josselin. "This is the man with whom one should discuss the
launching of a new democratic process."
</P>
<P>
But France deplored the "gearing of events in Congo since the
beginning of June" as well as intervention by foreign troops in
Congo, said Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
He said that France was maintaining contact with the Angolan
government over the security of about 1,600 French nationals
trapped in Pointe-Noire, the oil capital of Congo, which was
captured by Angolan troops on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a message to United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan,
the Angolan government accepted, Wednesday evening, that its
troops intervened in Congo. It said they did so for "pursuing
aggressors." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
