<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Seed Rios Beaten at Hong Kong Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Marcelo Rios of
Chile was defeated by Byron Black of Zimbabwe 7-6 (7-2), 5-7, 4-6
Thursday in the Silber group of the Hong Kong Tennis Championships.
</P>
<P>
Rios, one of the top-ten players in the world, lost the match
and failed to book a berth in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
World No. 60 Black came back to his form after he lost the
opening set and trailed 1-4 in the second.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Brazil's Gustavo Kuerten, French Open champion, won
the Blue group with a 6-3, 7-5 victory over American Justin
Gimelstob; American Vincent Spadea, last year's runner-up,
thrashed Peter Tramacchi of Australia 6-2, 6-2 in the Red group.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 players were divided into four groups in the
round-robin tournament before the semifinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
