<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK to Ban Foreign Donations to Political Parties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The British government announced
Thursday that it would ban British political parties from
accepting donations from abroad and donations above 5,000 pounds
(8,100 US dollars) would also have to be made public.
</P>
<P>
"This is another step towards greater openness and transparency
in public life and demonstrates our determination to remove an
unnecessary layer of secrecy and undue influence in our political
system," Home Secretary Jack Straw said.
</P>
<P>
Straw added that the government would push a bill on donations
through Parliament as soon as possible and would ask the
Parliamentary Committee on Standards in Public Life to look at
"wider questions of party funding".
</P>
<P>
The committee would be asked to study the possibility of limits
on national election campaign spending and of state-funding of
political parties.
</P>
<P>
The move followed the Labor Party's election pledge to clean up
politics and donations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
