<HEADLINE> Sassou Declares Victory in Congo Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Former President Denis Sassou
Nguesso of the Congo Republic has declared victory in the
four-month civil war and promised to set up "a government of
national union" in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
He made the declaration after his troops captured the capital
city of Brazzaville and the oil port of Pointe-Noire.
</P>
<P>
"For us, the war is finished, for we have the control of almost
the totality of the country, the total control of the political
capital (Brazzaville), the total control of the economic capital
(Pointe-Noire)," he told Radio France Internationale.
</P>
<P>
"In a few days, we will establish a government of national
union which will run a period of transition," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he didn't know about the whereabout of his rival,
President Pascal Lissouba, who has been on the run after his
troops were defeated in Brazzaville by militiamen of Sassou
Nguesso early this week.
</P>
<P>
The power struggle between the two erupted on June 5 when
Lissouba soldiers surrounded Sassou's home in a crackdown on
private militia. It derailed a July 27 election which both men
planned to contest.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to broker a truce floundered on differences over power
sharing in the run-up to a new election in the central African
country, which used to be a French colony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
