<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Home Resales Flat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The pace of home buying in
Canada remained flat last month, according to the latest report
from the Canadian Real Estate Association.
</P>
<P>
The association reported 18,410 homes were resold in September,
unchanged from August and up 4.1 percent from the same month a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, house resales across the country have risen
from the previous month only twice, in April and July. They have
fallen slightly in every other month.
</P>
<P>
But this year's numbers are consistently higher than those of a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
"Activity levels have run relatively steady since May," said an
economist with the association, adding that the levels are
healthy.
</P>
<P>
The resale numbers will remain on an even keel through the rest
of the fall, but is expected to pick up early next year.
</P>
<P>
"The fundamentals couldn't be better for housing," he said,
referring to low interest rates, strong job growth and good
housing affordability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
