<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Plays Up Governing by Law (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- In an October 17 editorial,
People's Daily, China's leading newspaper, calls for a governing
by law and socialist democracy.
</P>
<P>
The editorial, entitled "Making Great Efforts to Accelerate the
Process of Governing by Law", quotes President Jiang Zemin's
report to the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) as saying, governing by law is the fundamental
principle of the Party in leading the people and administering the
country.
</P>
<P>
Governing by law means that the broad masses, under the
leadership of the Party, run state affairs in various ways in line
with the Constitution and the law so as to gradually achieve the
systematization and legalization of socialist democracy, Jiang
said. He added the system and the law will not be changed simply
with a change of leaders.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that the supreme authority of the
Constitution and the law must be safeguarded and that all state
affairs must be conducted in line with the law.
</P>
<P>
This principle is different from the practice of the past,
when state affairs were governed by individual decisions and not
by law, the editorial says .
</P>
</TEXT>
