<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Developing a socialist democracy, perfecting the socialist
legal system, and administering the country by law are important
component parts of Deng Xiaoping Theory and have been the fundamental
principle of the Party since the 3rd Plenary Session of the 11th
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China held in 1978,
the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping said in the early years of reform and
opening-up, China should reinforce democracy and the legal system,
the two sectors the country had neglected in the past.
</P>
<P>
In the past 20 years, especially since the 14th CPC National
Congress in 1992, China has made great progress in establishing
a socialist legal system based on the Constitution, it says.
</P>
<P>
The 15th CPC National Congress, which proposes building a
socialist country governed by law, it adds, marked the deepening
of the Party's understanding of building China's socialist polity
with its own characteristics and the country has entered into a
new period of building the socialist legal system by focusing on
implementing the law.
</P>
<P>
The principle of governing by law is a requirement for the
socialist market economy, an important symbol of progress, and an
important guarantee for long-term stability, the editorial stresses.
</P>
<P>
The People's Congressional System should be adhered to and
perfected to guarantee its authority, it says. By 2010, a legal
system with Chinese characteristics is expected to take shape.
</P>
<P>
The dignity of the Constitution and the law must be
safeguarded, and everyone is equal before the law and no
individuals and organizations have the right to violate the
law, the editorial points out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
