<HEADLINE> Hingis donation to Aid Vaccination Programme </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- World tennis number one Martina
Hingis is donating 75,000 U.S. dollars to a vaccination programme
aimed at eradicating polio in Ethiopia, said the World Health
Organisation Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sum amounts to Hingis' winnings from an Arthur Ashe charity
tournament held in Flushing Meadow last August.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Swiss star, who is competing this week in the
Zurich WTA tournament, also agreed to act as a "roving
ambassador" for the WHO to help promote their vaccination
programme.  
</P>
</TEXT>
