<DOCNO> XIE19971017.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Special "Temple of Heaven" Stamp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 16 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications today issued a new set of four stamps depicting
the Temple of the Heaven, one of the best-known historical sites
in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
They were designed by Wang Huming, a well-known stamp
designer, and Ma Gang, an associate professor with the
Central Art Institute.
</P>
<P>
An issuing ceremony was held at the Temple of the Heaven, which
is an old imperial ceremonial site in Beijing, built during the
Ming Dynasty (1368-1644).
</P>
<P>
The 273 ha. site is four-times the size of the Forbidden
City. It is listed a candidate for the UN's World Heritage Site
list. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
