<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece, Slovakia Sign Economic Cooperation Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Slovakia today signed
an economic and commercial cooperation agreement as part of
efforts to expand their bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The pact was signed here by Greek National Economy
Undersecretary Christos Pachtas and visiting Slovakian Foreign
Minister Zdenka Kramplova.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros Pangalos today also
discussed with Kramplova the ways of broadening cooperation
between the two countries and the enlargement of the European
Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Pangalos told reporters after the meeting that Athens supported
Slovakia's efforts to join the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) and in favor of the simultaneous commencement of
negotiations for the accession to the EU of all candidate
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
