<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mutual Fund Sales Up in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Mutual fund sales in Canada
continued to be strong in September, with investors sticking with
higher-risk equity funds as their favorite choice, local reports
said today.
</P>
<P>
Net new fund sales for September totaled 3.87 billion dollars
(2.79 billion USD), up from 2.89 billion dollars a year earlier
and 3.4 billion dollars in August.
</P>
<P>
Strong sales and good market performance sent total industry
assets up 5.2 percent in September from August to 283.72 billion
dollars, according to the Investment Funds Institute of Canada.
</P>
<P>
And Canadian investors continued to favor equity funds,
channeling 1.03 billion dollars into Canadian equity funds, the
most popular type of fund in September.
</P>
<P>
They shied away from the lower risk, lower yielding money
market funds which drew in only 57.7 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, they also favored balanced funds that invest
in stocks and bonds as well as foreign equity funds, the institute
said.
</P>
<P>
A strong bull stock market, combined with low interest rates,
helped to propel the growth of mutual fund industry in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
