<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 80 Percent Ethiopians Use Traditional Medicines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Close to 80 percent of the
total population in Ethiopia are users of traditional medicinces.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Abebe Demese, deputy general director of
the Ethiopian Bio Diversity Institute when he was opening the
Ethiopian Traditional Medicine Preparation and Research Society's
annual meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
The traditional medication system is gaining a wider
acceptance especially among the rural society which prefers using
traditional remedies to modern medical treatment, Abede said,
adding that the exorbitant price of drugs and their unreliable
remedial value have forced the public to resort to traditional
healers.
</P>
<P>
Previously traditional treatment and its experts were denied
the proper attention, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the readiness of his institute to incorporate
unrecognized professionals into the society and extend every
necessary support to help the realization of its plans and
projects.
</P>
<P>
There are about 250 species of plants in Ethiopia which are
useful for the preparation of traditional medicines.
</P>
<P>
At present, the Ethiopian Traditional Medicine Preparation and
Research Society has over 900 members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
