<HEADLINE> Chinese Olympic Champions Strike Gold Double </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Olympic table tennis champions
Wang Tao and Deng Yaping both stroke a gold double after winning
the men's singles and women's doubles respectively at the National
Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Army veteran Wang, who paired with Olympic champion
Liu Guoliang to win the men's doubles gold on Thursday, met fierce
challenge from rising star Ma Lin of Guangdong Province in the
singles final.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old Wang, who paced Chinese national squad to win
two team titles at the previous two World Championships in Tianjin
and Manchester, edged out the 17-year-old youngester 21-11, 18-21,
21-16, 21-23, 22-20 before a cheering crowd in the Jiading Sports
Hall near Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
World number one Deng, Atlanta Olympic and Machester World
Championship winner, also won her second gold medal at the current
games by winning the women's doubles crown, after retaining her
women's singles title on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Teaming up with Zhang Hui, Deng, the most successful paddler in
the world, grabbed the gold for her native Henan Province by
ousting defending champions Li Ju and Wu Na of Jiangsu Province
16-21, 21-12, 22-20, 21-17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
