<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Envoy Calls for New Initiative on Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 17 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Special Envoy on
Afghanistan Nobert Holl said today that a new methodology was
needed to bring an end to the civil war in Afghanistan, a report
from Kabul said.
</P>
<P>
Holl told a press conference in the Afghan capital of Kabul
that the U.N. practice of holding talks with the warring factions
has not been successful in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Peace would not come to Afghanistan until complete harmony
exists with the neighboring countries, Holl said.
</P>
<P>
The international community was endeavoring to induce the
concerned countries to coordinate with the U.N. peace process on
Afghanistan, Holl added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
