<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Presents 15 Buses to Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony for the
presentation of 15 buses from China was held today in Tajikistan's
capital, Dushanbe.
</P>
<P>
The agreement for the supply of five million Renminbi Yuan
(about 600,000 U.S. dollars) worth of buses was signed by the two
countries last September when Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov
visited China.
</P>
<P>
The 15 buses, made by Shang Rao Automobile Factory, Jiangxi
Province, started out on September 23 on their way across
mainland of China and through Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan, finally
reaching Dushanbe on October 14. The journey covered 6,800
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Chen Zhongcheng and the mayor of Dushanbe
attended the ceremony on behalf of the governments of the two
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
