<HEADLINE> China's Chongqing Attracts Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Officials from Chongqing, a
city in Southwestern China, which has been become a municipality
directly under the central government earlier, extended their warm
welcome to Hong Kong investors here today.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of Chongqing into the 4th municipality directly
under the central government in China following Beijing, Shanghai
and Tianjin will bring more opportunities to investors, Xu
Zhongmin, vice mayor of Chongqing, told a Hong Kong-Chongqing
Investment Exposition today.
</P>
<P>
He promised to provide excellent services and favorable
conditions for investors.
</P>
<P>
He said that his city will act in accordance with international
 practice and give national treatment to overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing will also protect the legitimate rights and interests
of overseas investors, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing covers an area of 82,400 square kilometers with 43
administrative districts, cities and counties, and has a population
 of 30.227 million.  
</P>
