<HEADLINE> CPC Central Committee Congratulates Democratic League Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) congratulated the Eighth National
Congress of the China Democratic League (CDL) today, praising the
closer co-operation with the League, which is one of the eight
non-Communist parties in China.
</P>
<P>
In a letter of congratulation, the CPC central Committee said
that the CDL has followed Deng Xiaoping Theory, held the patriotic
and socialist banners up, and has taken part in the country's
drive to promote socialist material progress and cultural and
ethnic progress.
</P>
<P>
The letter praised the CDL for developing the country's
political, economic, legal, scientific, technological,
educational, and cultural sectors, and its many useful proposals
to the CPC Central Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Vice-premier Jiang Chunyun, who is a member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, spoke at today's opening
session of the CDL National Congress, on behalf of the CPC Central
Committee, saying, "We believe that the new generation of CDL
leaders who will be elected will inherit the good tradition of the
party's older leaders of closely co-operating with the CPC."
</P>
<P>
According to Ding Shisun, Executive Chairman of the CDL
Congress, who spoke at the session, the party now has 131,300
members, a large number of whom are young.
</P>
<P>
The CDL will adhere to the principle of unswervingly following
the leadership of the CPC and the guidance of Deng Xiaoping
Theory, Ding said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
