<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Population Conference Ends in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) - Today was the last day of the
23rd General Population Conference of the International Union for
the Scientific Study of Population (IUSSP), which opened last
Sunday and attracted 1,400 demographers and population workers
from various countries.
</P>
<P>
Peng Peiyun, Chinese State Councilor and Minister in charge of
the State Family Planning Commission, said at the closing ceremony
that she thinks the conference will help the development of
population science and finding solutions to population problems
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
She said that, in dealing with the problem, China must
co-ordinate development, population, the economy, society,
resources, and the environment, and that Chinese demographers are
ready for more exchanges and co-operation with foreign colleagues.
</P>
<P>
The conference is IUSSP's most important activity. It was
founded in 1928. This meeting had a symposium on Chinese
demography, two plenary sessions, 23 formal sessions and 42
informal ones.
</P>
<P>
The next conference is scheduled for Brazil in 2001.  
</P>
</TEXT>
