<HEADLINE> Bavarian Bank to Build New German Center in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The state bank of Bavaria will
spend 70 million US dollars on a new German center in the Pudong
New Area in Shanghai, Volker Stoeckel, the bank's executive
vice-president, told a news conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Floor space of the center is estimated 50,000 sq.m. It will
help the growing number of mid-sized and small German enterprises
enter the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the center is scheduled to begin in April of
next year and is expected to be finished at the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The bank set up a German center in Tongji University in 1996,
which has helped 45 German companies open offices in Shanghai, 10
of which then set up companies in the city.
</P>
<P>
The bank plans to set up a similar center in Beijing. 
</P>
