<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia, New Zealand Sign Trade Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and New Zealand
today signed a new treaty on trade and economic cooperation to
replace the 1961 Bilateral Trade Agreement.
</P>
<P>
The agreement would provide for the enhancement of the
bilateral commercial relations and give impetus towards greater
collaboration between the two sides, Malaysian International Trade
and Industry Minister Rafidah Aziz said at the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia-New Zealand trade in 1996 rose by 19.2 percent to
1,524 million ringgit (about 476.25 million U.S. dollars) with
Malaysia's exports amounting to 605 million ringgit (about 189.06
million U.S. dollars and its imports from New Zealand to 919
million ringgit (about 287.19 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Rafidah said that New Zealand's investment in Malaysia remained
relatively small with capital investments from 1989 to 1996
amounting to 105 million ringgit (32.81 million dollars) for 10
approved projects.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's investments in New Zealand are concentrated in the
acquisition of commercial real estate.
</P>
<P>
Rafidah and New Zealand Trade Minister Lockwood Smith signed
the new agreement on behalf of their respective governments.
</P>
<P>
The New Zealand trade minister is in Malaysia for consultations
between ASEAN economic ministers and their counterparts from
Australia and New Zealand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
