<HEADLINE> HK Entering a New Era, Says Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong entered a new era of
increasing strength and self-confidence after it returned to China
on July 1, Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of China's Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), said here today.
</P>
<P>
Tung told about 700 business, trade, tourism and community
leaders at a luncheon that Hong Kong people are marching forward
with pride and confidence.
</P>
<P>
"We are proud of being at last reunited with China and
confident that tomorrow will be even better," he said.
</P>
<P>
After the handover, "our economy continues to grow, our
financial foundation remains solid, and our society remains
pluralistic," he said.
</P>
<P>
Recent surveys by Hong Kong University showed that 85 percent
of the population in the region was confident about the future,
the highest percentage for Hong Kong under any administration.
</P>
<P>
Tung attributed the increased confidence to the "Basic Law"
which provides a constitutional framework for the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Tung is on a three-day visit to Japan, the first trip to the
country as chief executive of the HKSAR. 
