<DOCNO> XIE19971017.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Shake Off Pressure to Keep Hopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHERAN, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The absence of three major
players puts China's World Cup finals hopes in doubt, but the
confidence is still held among squad for Friday's meeting with
group leader Iran here.
</P>
<P>
After six-time misery memories of failing to qualify for the
World Cup finals, each win over Saudi Arabia and Kuwait earlier
this month invested a real sense of hopes to China in the seventh
seeking.
</P>
<P>
But it seems a tall order for the Chinese team when it loses
full-backs Fan Zhiyi and Xie Feng and striker Li Ming in the match
against Iran for two yellows each taken from previous qualifying
matches.
</P>
<P>
The lose of Li, the one of China's best striker, puts more
pressure to the team's leading marksman Hao Haidong, who scored a
first-three-minute goal when China beat Kuwait 2-1 last Friday.
</P>
<P>
China, who run the same record to 2-1-1 with Saudi Arabia in
the Asian qualifying group A, look shabbier than ever in defense
in Friday's match but the team remains confidence mentally.
</P>
<P>
"Everyone is on the same level, and we will play a great
match," said midfielder Ma Mingyu. "We lost the first leg match to
Iran, so we have no pressure as before."
</P>
<P>
Liu Jun, a possible replace of Li's position at right wing,
said, "We won't be softened in defense though we'll play without
Fan, Xie and Li. Someone is also capable to play the place. All we
should do is to make a good preparation as possible as we can."
</P>
<P>
China's left back is expected to be placed by Wu Chengying, who
was just called three days ago from Shanghai Shenhua, China's
Serie A league club.
</P>
<P>
"Wu is active at left," veteran Xu Hong said. "And with Sun
Jihai at right and the steady midfield, we'll play a more
offensive match against Iran. But tt's too early to talk about
what we could take from them (Iran)."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it seems that the host team is suffering much more
pressure to deliver the win.
</P>
<P>
The 4-2 win in the first leg boosted Iran's fans, who believe
their team is a class up on technique and patience. To prove it,
Iran must sharpen their attack as they did in the first meeting.
</P>
<P>
The result between Iran and China may set the best opportunity
for Saudi Arabia to move up to the group leader. The Saudians will
play weaker Kuwait in Friday's other group match.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait stands fourth in the group with 1-1-2 collecting five
points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
