<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Expand Cooperation With Australia, New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 17 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN (Association of
Southeast Asian Nations) economic ministers and their counterparts
from Australia and New Zealand today agreed to expand their
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached during their third informal
consultations in Subang Jaya, some 20 kilometers south of the
Malaysian capital of Kuala Lumpur, according to a joint press
statement issued after their meeting.
</P>
<P>
The areas of cooperation include human resources development,
investment promotion, professional work and building construction,
electronic commerce and sanitary issue, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The ministers at the meeting stressed the significance of
enhancing dialogue among their business people in order to expand
trade and investment between the two regions.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to encourage greater strategic alliances, joint
ventures and investments between their companies.
</P>
<P>
The next ASEAN-Australia-New Zealand conference will take place
in the Philippines a year later.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Australia and New Zealand today expressed confidence
that ASEAN economies affected by the current currency crisis in
the region will "bounce back and put in another decade of great
and solid economic growth."
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines,
Singapore, Thailand, Vietnam, Myanmar and Laos.  
</P>
