<HEADLINE> Berger Takes Break From Formula One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Gerhard Berger of Austria is
taking a break from Formula One motor racing but will comeback
sometime in the future, the dirver announced in a news conference
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Berger, who was in the first-class racing for 13 year, has
refused a further contract with Benetton team early.
</P>
<P>
"I need a break. I am very tired and exhausted. I want to
dedicate myself to my family," he said. "It's necessary for me to
live without the sport for a while."
</P>
<P>
There were a lot of speculation during the past three months
about the future of the 38-year-old Austria.
</P>
<P>
It was said that Berger quit his career because he failed to
find a drive for the next season. 
</P>
