<HEADLINE> Social Science Research Council Conference In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Today was the last day of the
five-day 12th conference of the Asian Association of Social
Science Research Councils in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, whose theme was "Globalization and regional
culture: problems to emerge in the 21st century", drew 30 Chinese
and foreign scholars from its 16 member countries.
</P>
<P>
The participants discussed various economic, cultural and
social development issues in the Asia-Pacific region. They said
that globalization has had a profound impact on the Asia-Pacific
region and has brought changes to traditional life-styles and
personal relations of people there. 
