<HEADLINE> High-Yield Oil Well Enters Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 17 (Xinhua) -- A high-yield oil well with a
daily production capacity of 2,000 tons of crude oil and 300,000
cu.m. of gas has entered operations in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The Zhaodong C-4, which has the nation's highest daily
production capacity, is located in the Zhaodong Agreement Zone, a
Sino-American oil development zone in the Dagang Oil Field.
</P>
<P>
The well consists of eight oil layers and one gas layer with a
total depth of 86.5 meters.
</P>
<P>
The Dagang Oil Field and two American oil companies -- Apache
China Co. Ltd. and XCL China Co. Ltd. -- commenced drilling in
July and opened the well in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
