<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survey: Chinese Expect Friendly Sino-US Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese citizens expect a
friendly and cooperative Sino-US relations, according to a
recent survey conducted in three major Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based Zero Survey Group recently completed a random
survey of 1,500 Chinese citizens in Beijing, Shanghai and
Guangzhou showing that 27.1 percent of respondents view the United
States as a friend of China, with 13 percent expressing a negative
attitude towards Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Some 47.2 percent voiced agreement with experts concerning the
fact that China and the US share an equally competitive
partnership, with another 8.6 being unclear about the situation.
</P>
<P>
One analyst directing the survey said that most Chinese
citizens appreciate peaceful, respectful and rational
international communications based on dialog, and are sensitive
about the domineering attitude the US government adopts on issues
concerning China.
</P>
<P>
They also expressed concern over White House opinions
concerning human rights and trade issues, and disagreed with US
comments on domestic Chinese issues such as Taiwan and Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that 58 percent of respondents have a
relatively good impression of conditions and customs in the United
States. They also expressed special appreciation for US movies and
are eager to make friends with US citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
