<HEADLINE> Wu Yanyan Breaks Women's 200m Individual Medley World Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Wu Yanyan of Guangxi set a new
world record in the women's individual medley by clocking two
minutes 9.72 seconds at the Eighth National Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The previous world mark of 2:11.65 was set by China's veteran
swimmer Lin Lin in the Barcelona Olympic Games in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yan, who set the world record in the 400m individual medly
on Monday, clocked 2:11.27 to finish second, also breaking the
world record.
</P>
<P>
The third place went to Sun Guiling with a time of 2:13.94.
</P>
