<HEADLINE> Sudan Reshuffles Top Military Brass </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Lt General Sayid Ahmed Seraj
has been appointed chief of staff of the Sudanese armed forces to
replace Lt General Ibrahim Sulaiman Hassan, according to the Sudan
News Agency today.
</P>
<P>
This was one of a series of personnel changes in the top
military brass in the country prompted by recent consecutive
military failures in the civil war with anti-government forces in
southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Other changes include state minister at the Defense Ministry
and deputy chiefs of staff of the armed forces. The official news
agency downplayed the reshuffle as normal rotations among senior
officers.
</P>
<P>
The military lost several garrisons to the hands of the John
Garang rebel movement on the eve of formal negotiations between
the government and the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The reconciliatory talks are due to take place on 28 October in
the Kenya capital city of Nairobi under the sponsorship of the
IGADD (Inter-Governmental Authority for Drought and Development)
of east and central Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
