<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> MOFTEC Vice-minister Addresses Sino-US Trade Relations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), answered
questions concerning President Jiang Zemin's forthcoming US visit
and Sino-US commercial relations during today's State Council
Information Office news briefing.
</P>
<P>
Sun said Jiang's visit to US later this month will be an
important event in the history of Sino-US relations. China and the
United States share extensive common interests in maintaining
world peace, promoting prosperity and stability in the
Asian-Pacific Region and the world at large, solving social
problems of worldwide interest, and strengthening cooperation and
exchanges in areas such as trade, economics, technology, culture
and environment.
</P>
<P>
China is fully confident of bright future prospects for Sino-US
relations, said Sun, adding that Jiang's visit will strengthen
cooperation between China and the United States in all areas.
</P>
<P>
Sun noted that a Chinese commercial delegation will visit the
US in the near future. Zeng Peiyan, vice-minister of the State
Planning Commission will lead the delegation consisting of
government officials and representatives from large
export-oriented enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the visit is to inform businesses in both countries
that the Chinese government attaches great importance to
commercial cooperation with the United States and increasing US
exports to China.
</P>
<P>
Sun pointed out that many Americans are unaware of the fact
that China imports many US products.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope the delegation's visit will inform more
Americans of the importance of Sino-US relations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
