<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets US Pepsi's Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
met here this afternoon with Roger Enrico, chairman and Chief
Executive Officer of the Pepsi Co. Inc. of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Enrico who is on his first visit to
China, Wu said that the Pepsi has a long-term good cooperation
with China, hoping that the two sides can make further efforts to
expand bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Enrico said he is satisfied with Pepsi's business in China, and
he is confident in its cooperation with the Chinese side, adding
that he hopes to further expand bilateral cooperation in beverages
and food.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the Pepsi will increase its investment in
Shanghai, China's biggest business center.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's upcoming visit to
the US will push forward the development of Sino-US relations and
bilateral economic and trade ties, and it will also create better
conditions for the exchange and cooperation between business
communities of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Enrico said that the US business people are expecting Jiang's
visit, noting that a sound bilateral relationship is beneficial to
both sides.
</P>
<P>
The US visitor is here as guest of the China National Council
of Light Industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
