<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rally on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied on the
Singapore market after a sharp fall on Thursday, as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index rose by 23.15 points to close at
1827.39 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 163.34 million units,
valued at 445.03 million Singapore dollars (about 287.12 million
U.S. dollars). Declines continued to lead advances by 197 to 120,
while 298 other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Penguin was the most actively traded counter as it registered a
turnover of 15.76 million units. It was followed by RHB Capital
Warrant99 which had 8.8 million units traded. The Singapore
Telecom was next with 5.07 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
C Properties, the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC)
Foreign, and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign shared the
top spot on the gainers' list as each of them increased by 50
cents to finish at 17, 10.5, and 22.8 Singapore dollars
respectively. Keppel FELS and NatSteel rose by 22 cents each to
end at 4.82 and 3.62 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Bukit Sembawang was the biggest loser as it
declined by two dollars to close at 19.8 Singapore dollars.
SimeDar and TAC 200 lost 26 cents each to end at 3.02 Singapore
dollars and 2.84 U.S. dollars respectively. City Developments was
25 cents lower finishing at 8.65 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
