<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Further Relaxes Gold, Silver Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government on
Thursday announced further liberalization of the gold and silver
import policy, allowing 11 agencies to import gold and silver for
sale in the domestic market on payment of duty in rupees, the
local press said today.
</P>
<P>
The move is expected to help bring down domestic gold prices
and benefit gems and jewelry exporters in the country
tremendously.
</P>
<P>
Under the new scheme, three trading companies and eight banks
will now be allowed to import gold and silver and supply it to the
domestic market as well, apart from supplying it to exporters of
jewelry.
</P>
<P>
Before the announcement of the new scheme, imports of the
precious metals were allowed only with special import licenses or
for sales to jewelry exporters.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the new policy, Finance Secretary Montek Singh
Ahluwalia said these agencies will be allowed to import gold and
silver on consignment basis in response to the demand placed on
them by domestic buyers.
</P>
<P>
There will be no restriction on the quantity they would like to
import, he said, adding that the import duty can be paid in
rupees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
