<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Adopt Food Security Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique will implement a
special initiative for food security from the current crop year
in order to promote food production and rural development by
adopting improved technology.
</P>
<P>
This was made public on Thursday by Clementina Machungo, an
official with the Ministry of Agriculture and Fishery, who added
that the Italian government has provided 1.7 million U.S. Dollars
to the program.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the initiative will take three years to
complete and six counties out of three provinces in Mozambique
have been selected for sites to carry out the plan, she said.
</P>
<P>
She disclosed that the Mozambican government is negotiating
with the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO)
to add two more counties for the initiative.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that FAO has also begun to implement such food
security plans in 18 other developing countries which are short
of food recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
