<HEADLINE> Prime Minister Bird Leaves Shenyang for Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Lester Bird of
Antigua and Barbuda this morning left Shenyang, capital of
northeast China's Liaoning Province, for Shenzhen city, China's
first Special Economic Zone.
</P>
<P>
Bird and his delegation arrived in the Liaoning capital on
Wednesday and visited the Shenyang Economic and Technological
Development Zone, as well as factories and historical sites.
</P>
<P>
Bird exhibited great interest in the construction and rapid
growth of the development zone, and expressed his desire to learn
more about the zone's experience.
</P>
<P>
During separate talks with Governor Wen Shizhen, also secretary
of the Provincial Party Committee, and Shenyang Mayor Mu Suixin,
Bird reaffirmed that Antigua and Barbuda pursue the "One China"
policy.
</P>
<P>
Bird joined the Shenyang city government in signing a framework
agreement calling for mutual economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China has agreed to open a representative office in Antigua and
Barbuda, and the two sides will exchange economic study and
research delegations.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for China to establish bonded warehouses,
processing bases, supermarkets, entertainment centers and
financial institutions, in addition to participating in
construction projects in the nation's free-trade zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
