<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Iraq Sign Oil and Rice Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Iraq have signed a
memorandum of understanding on oil and gas cooperation, reports
said today.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed here by Vietnamese Deputy Prime
Minister Nguyen Cong Tan and his Iraqi counterpart Mohammed Al
Zubaidi on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also signed a rice deal, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi deputy prime minister's visit to Vietnam was
described by Vietnamese media as "a turning-point for further
expanding the ties between the two countries in the future".
</P>
<P>
Al Zubaidi, who arrived here Monday for a six-day official
visit, has met with Vietnamese Communist Party leader Do Muoi and
Prime Minister Phan Van Khai. 
</P>
