<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Have Bigger Say in Family Life (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
However, the final decision on child-bearing is mainly up to
the woman, who has the final say on the timing of the pregnancy,
giving birth and becoming a mother.
</P>
<P>
The survey revealed a major shift in the thinking of today's
females in China regarding questions such as "whether a woman
should end up with one man."
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, most urban women and nearly half of
rural women hold negative attitude toward having only one man in
their life. In the divorce cases during the last 10 years, the
number of women who are initiating the divorce has been increasing.
</P>
<P>
Women consider contraception liberating, allowing them to
regulate child-bearing. The survey reveals that, besides the
safety period method, 40.88 percent of urban men, 44.59 percent of
urban women, 23.51 percent of rural men and 69.01 percent of rural
women are found to use some form of contraception. However, the
main responsibility of contraception still falls on women.
</P>
