<HEADLINE> Sino-Foreign Investment Bank Enters Domestic Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The nation's first Sino-Foreign
investment bank -- China International Capital Corp. (CICC) -- has
established a niche in the domestic capital market as an
authorized lead underwriter for A Share placements.
</P>
<P>
The corporation recently acted as the support underwriter for
two A share issues restricted to domestic investors.
</P>
<P>
Experts hailed the event as the starting point for the
convergence of the domestic and international capital markets, and
as a strong signal that more Sino-foreign investment banks will
enter the domestic capital market.
</P>
<P>
CICC, a joint venture between the China Construction Bank and
US-based JP Morgan, has actively tapped the international capital
market since its establishment in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The corporation acted as the financial consultant and
coordinator for the China Telecom (Hong Kong) acquisition of a 5.5
percent stake in Hong Kong Telecom. International syndicated loans
were used to purchase the share position from Britain's Cable and
Wireless, the parent company.
</P>
<P>
CICC was also one of the lead underwriters and the global
coordinator for the public share offering of China Telecom (Hong
Kong) in both Hong Kong and New York. The offering is expected to
raise the largest volume of overseas funds ever raised by a
Chinese company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
