<HEADLINE> China Sets Environmental Protection Goals for Next Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to raise its
environmental quality to levels required for ensuring the progress
of modernization in the middle of the next century.
</P>
<P>
A new blueprint issued by the State Bureau for Environmental
Protection (SBEP) calls for China to curb environmental
deterioration and dramatically improve environmental quality in
the first decade of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The country will control pollution and ecological damage by
2020, in addition to further improving environmental quality in
its urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
China will be a prosperous and democratic socialist country by
the middle of the next century, with environmental quality meeting
the needs for modernization process, according to the blueprint.
</P>
<P>
SBEP Deputy Director Zhang Kunmin said that China will enhance
pollution control and ecological protection efforts, and will do
its utmost to curb environmental deterioration and improve
regional environmental quality in the remaining years of this
century.
</P>
<P>
Last year alone, China closed more than 60,000 factories
causing serious pollution to the environment.
</P>
<P>
All industrial polluters in the Huaihe River Valleys have been
instructed to meet State emission standards prior to December 31,
1997,  
</P>
</TEXT>
