<HEADLINE> Ding Meiyuan Wins Last Weightlifting Title in World Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Ding Meiyuan of Liaoning
province took the last women's weightlifting title in world
records at the Eighth National Games here Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
In the women's over 83-kg class, Ding beat national record
holder Li Yajuan by lifting 137.5 kgs in snatch and 170 kgs in
jerk for a two-lift total of 307.5 kgs.
</P>
<P>
The previous listed world records were 112.5 kgs in snatch 155
kgs in jerk, and 260 kgs in the total.
</P>
<P>
As the women's weightlifting competitions concluded this
afternoon, all the world records in the 46kgs, 50kgs, 54kgs,
59kgs, 64kgs, 70kgs, 76kgs and 83kgs were surpassed by the Chinese
strongwomen in the previous four days.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women lifters have estabished their overhelming
dominance in the world as the sport will make its debut in the
2000 Olympic Games in Sydney. 
</P>
</TEXT>
