<DOCNO> XIE19971017.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 98 Percent of Poor Population Black: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 17 (Xinhua) -- About 45.7 percent of
South Africans live in poverty, but 98 percent of them are black,
according to statistics.
</P>
<P>
South Africa has a population of about 42 million, 75 percent
of which are black and 14 percent are white.
</P>
<P>
The opposition National Party released a report Thursday in
parliament based on statistics which in turn found it source to a
research conducted by the Human Sciences Research Council up
until 1994, Sowetan newspaper said today.
</P>
<P>
The province which has the highest figure is the Northern
Province with a 69.3 percent poverty rate, followed by Eastern
Cape with 64 percent, Kwazulu-Natal with 50 percent and Northern
Cape with 48 percent.
</P>
<P>
Then comes Free State with 47.1 percent, Mpumalanga with 45.1
percent, and Northwest with 41.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The provinces with lowest poverty rates are Western Cape with
17.9 percent and Gauteng with 21.1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
