<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Promotes Bar Coding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Over 100,000 varieties of
Chinese products carry bar codes in line with international
standards.
</P>
<P>
China currently ranks the world's fourth largest promoter of
bar coding, following the United States, Japan and Germany. The
country joined the International Bar Coding Association in April
1991.
</P>
<P>
Over 35,000 Chinese manufacturers belong to a national
organization specializing in promoting the use of bar codes.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin municipalities, as well as
Guangdong and Henan provinces, have formulated regulations
requiring that all commodities sold in supermarkets and chain
stores carry bar codes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
