<HEADLINE> More Firms in Central Province Seek ISO9000 Certification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of local
enterprises in Hunan Province in central China are working hard
for the certification of ISO9000 to be more competitive on the
international market.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 40 enterprises in Hunan Province have
received ISO9000 quality certification. Another 90 enterprises,
mostly exporters, have applied for certification.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises have reduced their production costs and
improved quality, according to local experts.
</P>
<P>
A local electromagnetic coil manufacturing company, for
instance, has reduced its reject rate from 23 percent to 8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Acquiring ISO9000 certification has been considered an access
to the international market by many local enterprises, the experts
say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
