<HEADLINE> China Plants Green Cotton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, October 17 (Xinhua) -- A strain of green cotton
introduced from the United States has been planted in northwest
China's Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
Colored cotton has been grown on a large scale in the United
States since the beginning of the 1990s. Clothes made from such
cotton has natural color with no need for printing and dyeing. As
a result, clothing costs have been lowered and pollution reduced.
</P>
<P>
Two years ago, China began planting colored cotton and set up a
colored cotton company in Gansu Province. Clothing made from the
colored cotton has attracted attention both at home and abroad at
the China '97 International Garments Fair, which was held last
spring in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
