<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 08:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Riyadh Insists on Boycotting Doha Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia said that it
will boycott the Middle East and North Africa Economic Summit
scheduled in Doha, Qatar in November which would include Israel.
</P>
<P>
The official Saudi Press Agency today quoted an official source
as saying that the kingdom will not be represented at any level at
the conference.
</P>
<P>
This was a downright denial of what U.S. State Department
spokesman James Robin said one day earlier that Saudi Arabia would
have some form of representation at the proposed conference.
</P>
<P>
The official source, who was not named, said "there is no
change in Saudi Arabia's position." Riyadh announced its boycott
after the Middle East peace process stalled due to Israeli
intransigence.
</P>
<P>
The annual event, launched in 1994, is traditionally attended
by Arab states, Israel and their major trade partners in the
industrialized world.
</P>
<P>
Several Arab countries, including Saudi Arabia and the United
Arab Emirates, expressed their intention to boycott in line with
the Arab League decision to suspend normalization of relations
with Israel following the Jewish state's construction of a new
Jewish settlement in Arab East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia is an Arab heavyweight and a member of the
six-member Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) which includes Kuwait,
the United Arab Emirates, Oman, Bahrain and Qatar.
</P>
<P>
Qatar has time and again expressed its resolve to host the
conference, but at a lower level of foreign ministers and said its
decision was made in the light of "progress in the peace process."
</P>
<P>
The conference, which symbolized an Arab-Israeli rapport, has
been vehemently supported by the United States. U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright met GCC foreign ministers in Saudi Arabia
last month during her first Mideast tour to persuade the Arab
countries to take part in the summit.

17/10/97 8:36 GMT

=10170839
NNNN
16:36 16:36 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
