<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Determined to Contain Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The government is determined
to contain the spread of cholera in western Kenya within two
weeks time, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here Thursday, Basil Criticos, Assistant
Minister for Health, confirmed that so far 140 people have died
of the epidemic during the past three months in parts of Nyanza
and Rift Valley provinces.
</P>
<P>
About 2,500 people suffering from the disease are currently
admitted at various health facilities in the affected areas, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
The health official told Kenyan parliament that the government
would declare the epidemic a national disaster and seek help from
the World Health Organization (WHO) if the situation is not
contained in the coming 10 days.
</P>
<P>
He said that his ministry has spent 12 million Kenyan
Shillings (about 200,000 U.S. Dollars) in the fight against the
disease and more funds are being sought from the Treasury.
</P>
<P>
Criticos said that the Health Ministry has formed task force
teams for the planning and coordination of control of the
epidemic.
</P>
<P>
The teams are responsible, among other things, for case
management, contact follow-up preventive treatment and community
health education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
