BEIJING -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji met here Friday with
Klaus Schwab, chairman of the World Economic Forum (WEF).
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Zhu, who briefed China's policy of reform
and opening up, and efforts to modernize the country, asked the
forum to support and stimulate China's reform process.
(China-WEF-Zhu)
</P>
