BUENOS AIRES -- U.S. President Bill Clinton attended two
working meetings Thursday with his Argentine counterparter Carlos
Menem to discuss regional economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state discussed topics on the Free Trade Area
of the Americas (FTAA) and the Southern Common Market (Mercosur).
(US-Argentina-Talks) 
