<HEADLINE> Reception Marks Sino-Ugandan Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a
reception here today to mark the 35th anniversary of the
establishment of Sino-Ugandan diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, Xie Bangding, vice-president of the
Sino-African Friendship Association, said that since the forging
of Sino-Ugandan diplomatic ties, bilateral relations of
cooperation have grown continuously.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Uganda have seen fruitful exchanges and
cooperation in many areas, including politics, trade and economy,
culture and education as well as health, Xie said.
</P>
