<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Oil-Processing Capacity Ranks 4th in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- China's annual crude oil
processing has reached 210 million tons, fourth in the world, the
China Economic Times has reported.
</P>
<P>
China now produces 3.94 million tons of ethylene each year,
also fourth in the world. Ethylene is a gas used in synthesizing
organic compounds.
</P>
<P>
Those figures for crude oil and ethylene reflect the rapid
growth of the industry since China Petrochemical Corp. was founded
in 1983.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the corporation processed 175 million tons of
crude oil, accounting for 80 percent of the country's total, and
2.95 million tons of ethylene, 75 percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The corporation has made major strides in technical ability,
said Sheng Huaren, general manager of China Petrochemical.
</P>
<P>
China has developed its own oil-refining equipment, Sheng said,
and has the ability to design large modern oil refineries.
</P>
<P>
China also has imported foreign technology and equipment since
the 1980s to boost its petrochemical industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
