<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Seek Assistance From Aid Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government will
seek only 1.46-billion-U.S.-dollar assistance at a Bangladesh Aid
Group meeting to be held here on November 4 and 5, the local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to a memorandum finalized by a special cabinet
meeting Thursday, the government utilized 1.3 billion dollars
provided by the aid group last year while the total commitment was
for 1.95 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The meeting maintained that it would be better to adopt a
pragmatic approach with regard to aid rather than obtain a big
commitment from the donors and that the amount of the aid to be
sought should be kept within limits, the newspaper The Independent
quoted sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Though it obtained a commitment for a large amount of loans
last year, the government failed to use the whole amount due to
the inefficiency of the implementing agencies, according to the
sources. 
