<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Philippines to Promote Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar and the Philippines
agreed to explore ways and means to further promote their
cooperation in various fields, said a joint communique issued
today at the end of Philippine President Fidel Ramos' three-day
state visit to Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The two sides in the communique expressed satisfaction over the
president's visit and said there exists sufficient scope for the
expansion of friendly contacts and cooperation in various fields
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the visit marked the beginning of a new
chapter in the relations between Myanmar and the Philippines and
will contribute to their efforts to further promote the friendly
relations and mutually beneficial cooperation between the two
countries and peoples, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides voiced their support for and commitment to the
realization of the goal of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations to achieve dynamic partnership in the political, economic
and social areas, it stated.
</P>
<P>
The communique said Than Shwe, chairman of the Myanmar State
Law and Order Restoration Council, accepted the invitation of
President Ramos to pay a state visit to the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
During his visit in Myanmar, President Ramos held talks with
Chairman Than Shwe on current regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also reached accords on trade, the
establishment of a joint commission for bilateral cooperation,
cooperation between the two governments against drug trafficking
and abuse and the promotion of technical cooperation in forestry
and forest-industrial development.
</P>
<P>
President Ramos arrived here Wednesday on the second leg of his
 tour of Hong Kong, Myanmar and Laos.  
</P>
