<HEADLINE> Trade Between Czech Republic, Poland Increasing Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Trade volume between the Czech
Republic and Poland this year is expected to rise 20 percent
compared to last year, a Polish diplomat said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jerzy Golis, the Polish embassy's commercial counsellor in the
Czech Republic, told reporters that the total two-way trade volume
of the two countries this year will exceed 2.5 billion U.S.
dollars, up 20 percent compared to last year.
</P>
<P>
During the first seven months of this year, trade volume
increased by 22 percent compared to the figure in the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
The total export volume of Poland to the Czech Republic during
the period increased by 25 percent compared to the same period
last year, and import volume is also up over 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Golis pointed out that there is great potential in trade
between the two countries, which can complement each other
economically. Poland is now the Czech Republic's sixth largest
trade partner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
