<HEADLINE> One Dead in Latest Attack on Serb Police Station in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 16 (Xinhua) -- An ethnic Albanian was killed
early today in an armed attack on a Serb police station in
southern Kosovo province, Serbia's Interior Ministry said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
A group of ethnic Albanians, armed with automatic rifles and
bomb-throwers, attacked the police station in the town of
Klincina, 40 kilometers from Kosovo's capital Pristina. One
attacker was killed in the fight.
</P>
<P>
The dead man was identified by police as Adrijan Krasnici, a
member of the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA), the Yugoslav news
agency Tanjug quoted the statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
The attack was the latest of a series of armed incidents in
troubled Kosovo, where ethnic Albanians, which constitute more
than 90 percent of its 1.9 million population, are seeking
independence from Serbia.
</P>
<P>
Armed attacks on police stations across Kosovo have increased
in recent months. The underground KLA has claimed responsibility
for some of the violence. 
</P>
