<HEADLINE> Philippine Trade Deficit Narrows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' trade deficit
in the first eight months of the year narrowed down by 5.6 percent
to 7.759 billion U.S. dollars from 8.21 billion dollars during the
same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
However, trade deficit for August alone recorded a 0.3-percent
increase to 1.029 billion dollars from 1.026 billion the previous
year, data released by the National Statistics Office showed
today.
</P>
<P>
according to the data, merchandise trade for the first eight
months grew by 16 percent to 39.809 billion dollars from 34.318
billion dollars a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Payments for imported goods went up by 11.8 percent to 23.784
billion dollars from 21.268 billion dollars while receipts from
exports jumping by 22.8 percent to 16.025 billion dollars from
13.05 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Aggregate trade value for August stood at 5.545 billion dollars
or 21.2 percent higher than 4.574 billion dollars last year, the
data showed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
