<HEADLINE> Chinese Woman Sprinter Breaks 100m Asian Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- China displayed its upperhands
in the women's 100 meters in Asia with a new mark set by in the
heats as the athletics competitions of the National Games started
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Li Xuemei clocked 10.90 seconds in the morning's heats,
bettering the listed Asian mark of 11.02 established by her
compatriot Liu Xiaomei in Beijing four years ago.
</P>
<P>
