<HEADLINE> Schneider Expanding Business in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- France-based Schneider Group,
the world's leading electrical transmission and distribution
equipment manufacturer, plans to further expand its investment in
China by establishing new joint ventures, according to today's
"China Daily".
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the company established a joint venture, Schneider
Shanghai Power Distribution Electrical Apparatus Co in Kang Qiao
Industrial Zone of Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
It is Schneider's second factory in the world to produce
Masterpact brand low voltage air circuit breakers.
</P>
<P>
Schneider's new joint venture is slated to go into operation
late this year in the Beijing Economic Development Zone. A wholly
owned manufacturing company is also planned for the Waigaoqiao
bonded zone in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
They company has now built six joint ventures with Chinese
partners. Shanghai hosts three of them, the others are located in
Tianjin, Guangzhou and Beijing.
</P>
<P>
And it also has a representative office in Chengdu, the capital
of Sichuan Province. Another one in Chongqing is expected to be
opened this year. 
