<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Police Arrest 3 Bombing Suspects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police Thursday
night arrested three Tamil rebels suspected of involvement in a
massive bomb blast in Colombo on Wednesday, police said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The three suspects, who are reportedly members of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), were arrested on a train
bound for the north.
</P>
<P>
Five LTTE rebels were killed on Wednesday by the security
forces in exchange of fire after the bomb explosion in the
downtown business center of the Sri Lankan capital.
</P>
<P>
Police are continuing their hunt for more suspect bombers
hiding in Colombo. So far they have rounded up 83 suspects from
various parts of Colombo who were unable to give valid reasons for
their presence in the city.
</P>
<P>
The bombing claimed 16 lives and injured 108 others, including
32 foreigners. Many buildings in the business area were seriously
damaged.  
</P>
