<HEADLINE> SFOR Finds Underground Arsenal in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, October 16 (Xinhua) -- A patrol of Multinational
Stabilization Force (SFOR), consisting of Russian and
U.S. soliders, has discovered an unreported underground arms depot
four kilometers south of the Udrigovo television tower.
</P>
<P>
The SFOR in Tuzla said in a news release today that the depot
contained 250 anti-tank mines, 46 boxes of TNT expolosives and 21
barrels of enriched petroleum for making napalm bombs.
</P>
<P>
The SFOR has confiscated the arms and moved them to the Bedroc
base near Tuzla, said the Croatian HINA news agency.
</P>
<P>
It is not clear who is the owner of those arms, HINA said.
</P>
