NAIROBI -- Leading tourism officials from Kenya, Tanzania and
Uganda Thursday reached a memorandum of mutual understanding to
promote their cooperation on wildlife protection and eco-tourism.
</P>
<P>
The three eastern African countries should market the region as
one destination for tourists and cooperate with each other more on
personnel training and wildlife security, they agreed at the end
of the East African Wildlife Cooperation meeting. (Kenya-East
Africa, Wildlife) 
