<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Ranked 3rd in Competitiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica is ranked the third
place in Latin America's "index of competitiveness" prepared by
the World Economic Forum and the Harvard Institute for
International Development published here today.
</P>
<P>
The index measures, among other things, the degree of
commercial opening, the rating of manpower, the functioning of the
institutions, the status of infrastructure and the situation of
the financial markets.
</P>
<P>
According to the index, Costa Rica is only surpassed by Chile
in Latin America, which holds the 13th place among 58 countries
studied, and Mexico, which is 33rd.
</P>
<P>
The first places at a world level are held by Singapore, Hong
Kong of China and the United States. 
</P>
