<HEADLINE> Chen Lu Leads Olympic Qualifying Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- China's Chen Lu led skaters
competing for the last berths of women's figure skating at next
year's Nagano Winter Olympics after the short program at an event
here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The event, open to all skaters, serves the Olympic qualifying
round and the best six skaters entering for the qualifying
competition would book their tickets to Nagano.
</P>
<P>
Chen skated to third place overall but is the leader for those
seeking to qualify for the Nagano Games.
</P>
<P>
Skating to "Adios Nonino," Chen's marks for required elements
ranged from 4.7 to 5.1, and from 5.0 to 5.7 for presentation.
</P>
<P>
American Tonia Kwaitkowski, who is not entered in the
qualifying competition, led the whole field with a clean, though
not brilliant program to Japanese music.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Zoe Jones was second, landing a triple lutz-double
toe loop combination and a triple flip.
</P>
<P>
In the men's short program, Australian Anthony Liu skated
flawlessly to lead the event.
</P>
<P>
He was followed by American Dan Hollander, also not in the
qualifying event, in the second place. Russian Ruslan Novoselzev
was third.
</P>
<P>
In ice dancing, Belarussians Tatjana Navka and Nikolia Morozov
continue to lead after the original dance, to jive music. Vocal
music, allowed this year for the first time in skating history,
added a new dimension to the event.
</P>
<P>
Russians Ekaterina Davydova and Roman Kostomorov retained their
second position. Chait Galit and Sergy Sukhnovsky of Israel
remained the leading Olympic qualifiers, followed closely by
Britons Marika Humphreys and Philip Askew.
</P>
<P>
The finals for the men, pairs and ice dancing take place on
Friday. The women will skate again on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
