<HEADLINE> Jansher Advances to Egyptian Squash Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 16 (Xinhua) -- World number one Jansher Khan
overwhelmed Peter Nicol of Scotland to enter the final of the
Egyptian Open squash tournament in Alexandria on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's Khan beat the third seed Scot 15-8, 12-15, 15-11,
15-10.
</P>
<P>
Khan proved yet again that there is nobody to equal his
confidence and precision at the front of the court. He took the
first game 15-8 with eight outright winners and three penalty
points. But Nicol managed to win the second game 15-12 in 18
minutes.
</P>
