<HEADLINE> Two Colombians Die in Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Two Colombians were
killed and some 5,000 suffered losses when two rivers burst banks
in the rural areas of El Carmen de Bolivar municipality, official
sources confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Holmes Torres said that after an eight-hour rainstorm,
the waters of the Gibrantar and Sabaneta rivers damaged houses and
swept away livestock.
</P>
<P>
The mayor added that the flood caused a serious sanitary
problem around the village because most of the flooded
neighborhoods have no sewage systems and the wells have overflowed.
</P>
<P>
Department authorities said the Colombian government will have
to spend some 3 million U.S. dollars in solving the problem.
</P>
<P>
The Arenal River, to the south of the department, also
overflowed because of the recent rains.
</P>
<P>
Its waters flooded the Arenal municipality, where dozens of
people had to abandon their homes.
</P>
<P>
The Arenal municipality lost communications with outside after
rocks and tree trunks obstructed the only road to the village.
</P>
</TEXT>
