<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Crowns at Piedmont Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian Gianluca Bortolami broke
away from the lead pack with 8 kilometers left to outpace
compatriot Paolo Lanfranchi, crowning at the Tour of Piedmont
cycling race on Thursday in Turin, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Bortolami, who rides for the Festina team, clocked four hours,
34 minutes, 40 seconds after completing the 200-kilometer route in
and around the northern industrial city.
</P>
<P>
Mapei's Lanfranchi finished second with two seconds behind. It
is his second narrow loss in two days after finishing third behind
ONCE teammates Laurent Jalabert and Alex Zulle in the
Milan-to-Turin road race on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Another Italian, Biagio Conte of the Scrigno team, was 23
seconds back for third place.  
</P>
</TEXT>
