<HEADLINE> Pioline Advances to Quarter-finals at Lyon Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Cedric Pioline of France blew
past his compatriot Arnaud Clement 6-2, 6-2 at the second round of
ATP Tour in Lyon, France on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Though Clement tried to regain his form on the first round when
he eliminated top-seeded Australian Patrick Rafter, he was stopped
the way to the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Pioline will next play seventh-seeded Australian Mark
Philippoussis, who edged American Richey Reneberg 4-6, 7-6, 6-4,
in Friday's quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Second-seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia ousted Dutchman Fernon
Wieber 6-3, 6-4, and will face the winner of the evening match
between Tim Henman of Britain and Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seed Thomas Enqvist of Sweden beat American Todd Martin
7-5, 6-3, and will meet Tommy Haas of Germany who dispatched
Spaniard Julian Alonso 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The winner between Frenchman Fabrice Santoro and eighth-seeded
former Wimbledon champion Richard Krajicek will play Spaniard
Felix Mantilla in the other quarter-finals. 
</P>
