<HEADLINE> Brazil, Canada Sign Trade Exchange Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazil and Canada signed
here today an agreement to increase the trade exchange between two
countries, Brazilian Agriculture Minister Arlindo Porto said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, the minister said that under the
agreement, tariff and non-tariff barriers to the export of
Brazilian agricultural products to Canada could drop in January
next year.
</P>
<P>
Porto said that Brazil and Canada will sign a final agreement
on trade exchange in January when Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien visits Brazil.
</P>
<P>
A team of Brazilian and Canadian technicians will study in the
coming days the document on the barriers raised to Brazilian
fruits, juices, and meats in Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
