<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Sugar Sales Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's sugar processor, ZSR
Corporation today said sales of refined sugar on the domestic
market were buoyant, increasing by 12.6 percent over six months.
</P>
<P>
The company sold 111,593 tonnes of sugar during the six months
ended September 30, 1997, compared to the same period last year
when it sold 99,125 tonnes.
</P>
<P>
Secretary of the company Aldo Musemburi said a significant
portion of the increase came from industrial sales while overall
sales were boosted by a longer trading period which included one
additional week.
</P>
<P>
"Exports of refined sugar to neighbouring countries remained
at previous levels," he said.
</P>
<P>
Refined sugar exports were pegged at 15,256 tonnes during the
period under review as compared to 15,021 tonnes in the same period
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
He said, "the sugar business is assured of receiving adequate
supplies of raw materials for the remainder of the year."
</P>
<P>
He added that group profit before taxation increased by 31.3
percent to 65.7 million Zimbabwe dollars (5.2 million U.S.
dollars) during the period under review. 
</P>
</TEXT>
