<HEADLINE> Russian Opposition Offers Way Out of Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Russian main opposition,
including the Russian Communist Party, the Agrarians and the
People's Power faction, on Thursday approved a letter to President
Boris Yeltsin, showing a way out of the government "crisis", the
Itar-Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Communist leader Gennady Zyuganov, the letter
stressed that "it would be important to change an attitude to the
law on the government for a final decision to be taken on a
no-confidence vote in the government."
</P>
<P>
The authors of the letter believed, the report said, it would
be inadmissible to raise rent prices as well as prices for public
utilities, and asked for guarantees that they would not be raised
in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
The letter also stressed the need to reform the television and
Radio channels for covering parliamentary issues. At the same
time, observation councils should be set up on television with
participation of the opposition, Zyuganov said.
</P>
<P>
The letter urged to implement the idea of a round table
conference of leading political parties and organizations where
land issues, combating crime and corruption, as well as prices for
energy carriers could be discussed, Itar-Tass said.
</P>
<P>
The Communist faction leader expressed determination that they
would not withdraw their proposals on a no-confidence vote in the
government, but would like to hear the answers to these questions
before Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
Russian Federation Ivan Melnikov told reporters today that their
final decision would depend on the outcome of a meeting comprising
the president, the prime minister and the speakers from both
houses of parliament.
</P>
<P>
It will also depend on "a round table" conference of Russia's
political parties and organizations as well as on a decision of
the Communists' Central Committee a plenary meeting on Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
