<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
has given Tanzania 2.84 billion shillings (about 4.5 million US
Dollars) for improving urban water supply and sewage services and
rehabilitating cotton research facilities.
</P>
<P>
Two agreements were signed here today between the Principal
Secretary in the Tanzanian Ministry of Finance, Raphael Mollel
and head of the EU delegation, Peter Christiansen.
</P>
<P>
Under the first agreement, EU will provide 1.35 billion
Shillings to support reforms initiated by the Tanzanian
government for improving urban water supply and sewage services,
in four regions of Mtwara, Mbeya, Iringa and Mwanza.
</P>
<P>
Under the other agreement, EU will give Tanzania 1.49 billion
shillings for the transfer of resources for the loss of cottom
export earnings during 1991 and 1992.
</P>
<P>
"The overall objective of the program is to contribute to a
sustainable increase in cotton export earnings where assistance
will be provided to rehabilitate cotton research facilities,"
Christiansen said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be made to implement a new cotton seed
multiplication strategy and to rehabilitate lint testing
facilities at Ukiriguru and Ilonga, he said. 
