<HEADLINE> Egypt Stages Joint War Games with Six Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Egypt said today advanced weapons
and management are making a difference in its ongoing military
exercises jointly held with six other nations on its northern
coast and in the western desert.
</P>
<P>
"Bright Star 97," the largest war games ever staged in the
Middle East, will be participated by Britain, the United Arab
Emirates (UAE), the United States, France, Kuwait and Italy as
well as Egypt, said Coordinator of the Egyptian forces in the
exercises Ahmed Gamal said at a press conference here.
</P>
<P>
The initial period of the three-phased maneuvers was for
preparations and light training, which was commenced a week ago,
Gamal said.
</P>
<P>
Forces of Egypt, Britain and the UAE, backed by armored
vehicles, landed from air and sea to establish a beachhead and
prevent "enemy" troops from occupying the area of El-Alamein -
scene of a famous World War II battle, according to Gamal.
</P>
<P>
From October 24-31, the exercises will enter the second phase
to mobilize the vast majority of the participating forces and
bring the exercise to its peak intensity.
</P>
<P>
Two troops, formed as friendly "green" forces and enemy
"orange" forces, will fight a fierce war along Egypt's western
border and the northern coast. Ground, air and naval forces of
both sides will attack and counterattack each other in the areas.
</P>
<P>
The final phase on November 1-2 is a training program for
Egyptian and U.S. military commanders.
</P>
<P>
Gamal said that a salient objective of the exercises is to
improve the capability of planning, management and decision-making
of Egyptian military commanders, as they will be allowed a free
hand in running the combat operations.
</P>
<P>
The exercises are also designed to train the participating
forces their efficiency in carrying out reconnaissance operations,
mounting rapid defense, confronting attacking forces, landing from
sea and air and staging combat actions.
</P>
<P>
The war games will feature sophisticated and hi-tech military
hardware including Apache helicopters and George Washington
transport aircraft, and U.S.-made Taba and Mubarak destroyers
which joined of the Egyptian navy months ago, he said.
</P>
<P>
Electronic warfare methods will be fully employed, such as
early warning, eavesdropping and jamming while the air force will
gain experience in aerial photography, raiding, aerial combat and
interception, providing support to ground forces, dropping
paratroopers and mid-air refueling, and search and rescue.
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers are believed to act as a "duel military-political
deterrent" - flexing military muscle and signal possible
international alliance Egypt can draw on in case of an invasion.
</P>
<P>
The exercises, introduced in 1983, is held once every two
years by Egyptian and the U.S. troops. Some other countries began
to join in from 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971017.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
