<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Chinese Win Prize for Women's Creativity in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Four Chinese are among 33
laureates selected this year for the annual prize for women's
creativity in rural life awarded here on Wednesday by the Women's
World Summit Foundation (WWSF).
</P>
<P>
The four Chinese laureates are Aloniuniu from Sichuan Province,
Fang Xiulan from Gansu Province, Luo Xifen from Guizhou Province,
and Miao Changlian from Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Aloniuniu, of China's Yi Minority, has succeeded in covering
155 hectares of barren hills with various kinds of bushes and
trees since 1982. She shares almost whatever she has with other
villagers. With money earned by growing trees, she helped nine
families living in poverty to pay their agricultural taxes.
</P>
<P>
Fang started a chicken farm in 1986. With the number of
chickens increasing from 1500 to 10,000, she expanded her farm to
include ducks and pigs. By 1996, her assets amounted to one
million yuan (120,000 US dollars). To help her neighbors including
the handicapped get out of poverty, she initiated an Ecological
Breeding Cooperative. Now, The town in which she lives is known
for its chickens, with each household raising more than 130
chickens on average.
</P>
<P>
Luo is of China's Buyi Minority in Guizhou Province. She opened
a pepper sauce processing factory in 1993. Hundreds of her
neighbors began to sell their peppers to her factory to earn cash.
In 1996, each family earned at least 650 yuan (78 US dollars) from
selling peppers alone to her. With 30,000 yuan (3,600 US dollars),
she set up a scholarship program for children in poor families in
her county.
</P>
<P>
Miao is the Director of the Women's Federation of Enrong
Village, Jiangxi Province. She is not only a good organizor, but
also a good rice grower. In 1996, Miao harvested two tons of
hybrid rice seeds on her 0.6 acre of land and sold them for an
income of 20,000 yuan (2400 US dollars). She always helps others
and offers loans to villagers to improve their living standard and
help them towards self-sufficiency. In 1992, supported by a loan
from Miao, a small processing factory was set up to teach women in
the village practical skills.
</P>
<P>
The WWSF is one of the three international Non-Governmental
Organizations (NGOs) which proposed at the 4th United Nations
World Conference on Women in Beijing that a specific day each year
be designated to highlight the largely unrecognized contribution
of rural women, mainly farmers, the world over, to food security
and to the development of rural areas. The WWSF has suggested that
World Women's Day fall on October 15th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971017.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
