<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims 25 Lives in Mozambique's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MAPUTO, October 16 (Xinhua) -- About 25 people have died of
cholera in Mozambique's capital Maputo and its rural Matola town
since the disease broke out last October.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released by the Mozambican Health
Ministry, most of the victims are those in the countryside
where sanitation condition is poor.
</P>
<P>
A Health Ministry source said preventive and supervisory
measures have been taken to check cholera.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry has launched a publicity campaign
against the danger of the plague and warned areas not affected
to take preventive actions.
</P>
<P>
Cholera has also erupted in Tanzania, Burundi, Nigeria,
Democratic Republic of Congo. 
