<HEADLINE> Angolan Government to Offer More Aid to Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Agricultural Minister
Carlos Fernandes said here today that the government will offer
more help to farmers to help increase grain production.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Fernandes, addressing on the World Food Day, said that
Angola, a country with 60 to 70 percent of its population living
in the countryside, views it very important to increase grain
production.
</P>
<P>
Only when enough grain is produced, can every people enjoy the
adequate food producing a minimum of 2600 calorie a day, he said,
at present one Angolan can only takae 1740 calorie a day.
</P>
<P>
Fernandes said that a matter of first importance is to change
the country's over-dependance on on import and emergency food aid
into a self-sufficient grain producer.
</P>
<P>
He said that to accomplish the target, the government should
play its role to guarantee that there is stock and ample supply
at the same time.
</P>
<P>
The government will soon unroll plans for promoting trade,
agriculture, animal husbandry and small-scale enterprises to help
increase grain production.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Fernades said that the money-rigid government also
found it hard to meet the national need for meat supply, saying
that the country has to spend 40 million U.S. Dollars on
importing meat. 
</P>
