<HEADLINE> IDB Launches 1 Bln Dlr Global Bond Issue for 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) has announced the launching of a 1 billion
U.S. dollar global bond issue, the third global dollar issue by
the Bank and the second this year.
</P>
<P>
The bonds pay a semiannual coupon of 6.375 percent and mature
on October 22, 2007.
</P>
<P>
J.P. Morgan Securities Inc. and Merrill Lynch Pierce Fenner and
Smith are the joint lead managers of the issue, which was priced
at 99.373 percent.
</P>
<P>
This proceeds of the issue will be incorporated into the IDB's
ordinary capital and will be used to help finance the social and
economic development of the Bank's Latin American and Caribbean
member nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
