<HEADLINE> US Military Jet Crashes in Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. military jet crashed
today during a training flight near Wright Patterson Air Force
Base in Ohio, but the pilot ejected safely.
</P>
<P>
The Marine Corps AV-8B Harrier went down at 1:45 p.m. EDT (1745
GMT) when it was in a flight with three other aircraft. They were
departing the Air Force base when the pilot of the crashed plane
said he had a fire on board.
</P>
<P>
The AV-8B Harrier jet was assigned to the Marine Corps Air
Station at Cherry Point, North Carolina.
</P>
<P>
The Marine pilot was taken to the Wright Patterson Medical
Center with minor injuries. Eyewitnesses said the pilot ejected
about two seconds before the aircraft crashed into a field about
17 kilometers from Dayton in west-central Ohio. 
</P>
</TEXT>
