<HEADLINE> Fresh Registration of Voters Begins in Lesotho </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Fresh registration of voters
has begun in Lesotho for the general elections due to be held next
year, according sources reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The exercise had to begin again because the voters' roll had not
been updated, Southern African Broadcasting Association quoted Sekara
Mafisa, Chairman of the Independent Electoral Commission, as
reporting.
</P>
<P>
Mafisa said the voter registration is an ongoing process, which
needs to be reviewed from time to time.
</P>
<P>
An Independent Electoral Commission was launched last month to
oversee the entire polling process.
</P>
<P>
Lesotho's last polls, held in 1993, were supervised by the
Electoral Office under a chief electoral officer appointed by the
government.
</P>
<P>
Opposition parties claimed that the officer was biased in the polls
because he was a civil servant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
